    <h3>The Solitary Nature of Technical Work</h3>
    <p>The culture in technical consulting firms, while built on high standards and strong performance, can sometimes make it harder to address mental health openly. The pressure to meet billable targets, hit deadlines, and stay highly utilized often leaves little room for rest or reflection. Add to that the independent nature of technical work and a competitive environment, and it’s easy for professionals to feel isolated or even question their place. Many carry the unspoken expectation to always appear capable and composed, even when they’re struggling. Twennie recognizes these challenges and aims to open up space for healthier conversations, habits, and support systems within technical teams.
</p>
